1.text: In principio creavit Deus caelum et terram.
1.translation: In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.

2.text: Terra autem erat inanis et vacua, et tenebrae erant super faciem abyssi; et Spiritus Dei ferebatur super aquas.
2.translation: And the earth was without form and void, and darkness was upon the face of the deep; and the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters.

3.text: Dixitque Deus: 'Fiat lux.' Et facta est lux.
3.translation: And God said: Let there be light. And there was light.

4.text: Et vidit Deus lucem quod esset bona; et divisit lucem a tenebris.
4.translation: And God saw the light that it was good; and He divided the light from the darkness.

5.text: Appellavitque lucem diem, et tenebras noctem; factumque est vespere et mane, dies unus.
5.translation: And He called the light Day, and the darkness He called Night; and there was evening and morning, one day.

1.text: Igitur perfecti sunt caeli et terra, et omnis ornatus eorum.
1.translation: So the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the furniture of them.

2.text: Complevitque Deus die septimo opus suum quod fecerat; et requievit die septimo ab universo opere quod patrarat.
2.translation: And on the seventh day God ended his work which he had made: and he rested on the seventh day from all his work which he had done.

3.text: Et benedixit diei septimo, et sanctificavit illum, quia in ipso cessaverat ab omni opere suo quod creavit Deus ut faceret.
3.translation: And he blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: because in it he had rested from all his work which God created and made.

1.text: Sed et serpens erat callidior cunctis animantibus terrae quae fecerat Dominus Deus.
1.translation: Now the serpent was more subtle than any of the beasts of the earth which the Lord God had made.
